      <title>👫💕I’M GRATEFUL! I’M GRATEFUL! 👫💕I used to publish fiction comics when I was a te...</title>
      <link>https://www.instagram.com/p/DS7qUppDPzM/</link>
      <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/609009461_18549002899045494_7489275115878101207_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_p1080x1080_sh2.08_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=102&amp;ig_cache_key=Mzc5OTgxNjgzMzc4OTA5Njk5Mg%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjE0NDB4MTkyMC5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=MdOj6qiongUQ7kNvwGU0w6I&amp;_nc_oc=AdoL1hvkTmM7ug268iOPi_OvFv_dB7k7-EdtiV2u7MZdc7Dow61i8gnotsj9RfzCBXw&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=Bw8GqDvXaUti1bfeUl3Ubw&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfxZ1CvT25QZfMqlWpG0BVeeUtdo-XE_liUwqMUAwsaSVw&amp;oe=69C8FBE0" alt="Instagram billede fra @chat_pet_4" /></p><p><strong>@chat_pet_4</strong></p><p>👫💕I’M GRATEFUL! I’M GRATEFUL! 👫💕I used to publish fiction comics when I was a teenager, and now after 30 years I’ve come back to the fiction game and published a novel, and that makes me emote like a softie, and say, yes,  I adore my friends &amp; families &amp; my person—without you I’m NOTHING—it’s so much fun to write &amp; publish and read from books. Because a spectre is haunting the world: the spectre of FICTION—enter the battle—no time for indoor complaints! Thanks to everyone who made it possible to put out books in 2025 in such fun ways: Genoa, Plenge, Marianne Torp, my extremely, extremely generous Northwest Patron, The Fake Foundation, ArtXNYC, The Monaco-Mueser Collection, HuskMitNavn, The Danish Arts Council, A-Mock Book, Synth Books, my day job homies, The Penguin Consigliera in Astoria and also, ahem Joelle. And lastly, yes art might be a tad sick but art will NEVER die—it will mutate—get ready for the new beautiful monsters of art 2026.<br/>
<br/>
On the photos:<br/>
1: Jessie Gordon at the reception for Wild Victim Unit 2: Darsi Monaco at the merch stand same place<br/>
4: Books for sale at ArtxNYC<br/>
5: Kate Houghton inside the Statue of Liberty <br/>
6: My index card system for writing<br/>
7: Ivy Pham, Alyssa Davis, Alex Meurice &amp; Joelle Dong at WVU reception <br/>
8: Photo from Statue of Liberty Museum<br/>
9: Me reading at Wild Victim Unit reception <br/>
10: Me in Hamburg 2002<br/>
11: Copies of The Synth Criminals <br/>
12: A dramatic entrance at Flux Lumina by Kate<br/>
<br/>
@joelledong @henrikplengejakobsen @marianne.torp  @soouhi_  @wallnernicolai  @artxnyc @denfrie.cph  @amockbook @fakefoundation @fluxlumina @jake.mueser @darsimonaco @huskmitnavn1</p>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/609009461_18549002899045494_7489275115878101207_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e35_p1080x1080_sh2.08_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=102&amp;ig_cache_key=Mzc5OTgxNjgzMzc4OTA5Njk5Mg%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjE0NDB4MTkyMC5zZHIuQzMifQ%3D%3D&amp;_nc_ohc=MdOj6qiongUQ7kNvwGU0w6I&amp;_nc_oc=AdoL1hvkTmM7ug268iOPi_OvFv_dB7k7-EdtiV2u7MZdc7Dow61i8gnotsj9RfzCBXw&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=Bw8GqDvXaUti1bfeUl3Ubw&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_AfxZ1CvT25QZfMqlWpG0BVeeUtdo-XE_liUwqMUAwsaSVw&amp;oe=69C8FBE0" alt="Instagram billede fra @chat_pet_4" /></p><p><strong>@chat_pet_4</strong></p><p>👫💕I’M GRATEFUL! I’M GRATEFUL! 👫💕I used to publish fiction comics when I was a teenager, and now after 30 years I’ve come back to the fiction game and published a novel, and that makes me emote like a softie, and say, yes,  I adore my friends &amp; families &amp; my person—without you I’m NOTHING—it’s so much fun to write &amp; publish and read from books. Because a spectre is haunting the world: the spectre of FICTION—enter the battle—no time for indoor complaints! Thanks to everyone who made it possible to put out books in 2025 in such fun ways: Genoa, Plenge, Marianne Torp, my extremely, extremely generous Northwest Patron, The Fake Foundation, ArtXNYC, The Monaco-Mueser Collection, HuskMitNavn, The Danish Arts Council, A-Mock Book, Synth Books, my day job homies, The Penguin Consigliera in Astoria and also, ahem Joelle. And lastly, yes art might be a tad sick but art will NEVER die—it will mutate—get ready for the new beautiful monsters of art 2026.<br/>
